---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Tanzania Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/tanzania/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Kenya for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/kenya' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
  { title: 'Rwanda for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/rwanda' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'tanzaniaFit', header: 'Tanzania Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TZS$1.1M-1.57M/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TZS$1.29M-1.84M/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TZS$990K-1.41M/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TZS$920K-1.31M/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (AAR, Jubilee)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'TZS$250K-600K/mo', tanzaniaFit: 'Regional' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'TZS$990K-1.57M', annual: 'TZS$11.9M-18.8M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'TZS$1.36M-2.09M', annual: 'TZS$16.3M-25.1M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'TZS$1.83M-2.81M', annual: 'TZS$21.9M-33.7M' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'TZS$50K-150K/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'TZS$300K-800K/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Tanzania 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Tanzania. Serengeti, Zanzibar, Kilimanjaro, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Tanzania"
  subheadline="Tanzania offers iconic Serengeti, Zanzibar beaches, Mount Kilimanjaro, and diverse wildlife—premium African safari destination with tropical island lifestyle options."
  heroImage="/images/countries/tanzania-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Tanzania</h2>
  <p>
    Tanzania offers Africa's most iconic safari (Serengeti, Ngorongoro), tropical Zanzibar paradise, and Mount Kilimanjaro majesty. For adventurous retirees seeking premier African wildlife with beach retreat options, Tanzania delivers unmatched natural experiences.
  </p>

  <p>
    Dar es Salaam is commercial capital with best healthcare. Arusha is safari gateway. Zanzibar offers island lifestyle. Most expats choose Dar es Salaam for healthcare, Zanzibar for lifestyle, or Arusha for safari access. Healthcare limited outside main cities.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Nairobi backup common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Swahili and English (official)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> TZS$2M-4M/month (~$800-1,600 USD); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical coast; pleasant highlands</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Safari; beaches; diverse wildlife</li>
      <li><strong>Nairobi backup:</strong> 1-hour flight for complex care</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Tanzania Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Tanzania healthcare is limited—Aga Khan Hospital (Dar es Salaam) and Selian Lutheran Hospital (Arusha) are best options. Private care improving but specialists limited. Complex cases typically evacuate to Nairobi (1-hour flight) or South Africa. Zanzibar has basic healthcare.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare underfunded. Safari and remote areas have minimal healthcare. International insurance with strong evacuation to Nairobi essential. Kenya provides essential medical backup for serious conditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Nairobi Backup Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Kenya provides essential medical backup—Nairobi is 1-hour flight with excellent hospitals. Include Kenya in insurance coverage. Dar es Salaam handles routine care; Nairobi provides specialist backup. Safari areas require evacuation capability.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Tanzania has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    90-day single entry visa available on arrival or e-visa. $50 for most nationalities.
  </p>

  <h3>Multiple Entry Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Up to 1 year with multiple entries. Good for frequent travelers.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    Class A (employment), Class B (investment), Class C (other lawful occupation). Apply through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Zanzibar Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Zanzibar has semi-autonomous immigration. Residence permits available. Popular retirement option.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Tanzania:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Nairobi coverage essential</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Tanzania</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with strong Nairobi evacuation coverage essential. Local private care handles routine needs. Kenya provides specialist backup. Safari areas need robust evacuation. Don't economize on coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Tanzania, Kenya evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Tanzania</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Africa network, Nairobi access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Nairobi access:</strong> Regional medical hub</li>
    <li><strong>Safari coverage:</strong> Remote area evacuation</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with strong East Africa evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Tanzania (TZS ~2,500 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dar base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> East Africa focused</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Nairobi network:</strong> Use for specialists</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Zanzibar Beach Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month pension. Residence permit. Stone Town.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Dar/Nairobi evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TZS$1.2M/month (~$480). Island paradise; mainland backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Safari Lodge Manager, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $4,000/month income. Work permit. Serengeti area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global premium with maximum evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TZS$1.5M/month (~$600). Remote location; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Development Worker, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,200/month pension. Residence permit. Dar es Salaam.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with East Africa coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TZS$990K/month (~$395). City life; Nairobi accessible.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Tanzania safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—lower crime than Kenya. Tourist areas well-protected. Dar es Salaam has some petty crime. Zanzibar very safe. Safari areas secure. Normal precautions apply. Overall peaceful destination.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's Zanzibar like for retirement?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Tropical paradise—beautiful beaches, Stone Town UNESCO heritage, spice culture. More relaxed pace than mainland. Limited healthcare (ferry to Dar for serious care). Growing expat community. Semi-autonomous with own residency rules.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is English sufficient?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Mostly—English is official language alongside Swahili. Business and government in English. Healthcare providers speak English. Learning basic Swahili helpful for daily life. More Swahili-dominant than Kenya.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Tanzania compare to Kenya?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Tanzania has better safari (Serengeti vs Maasai Mara), Zanzibar beaches, lower crime. Kenya has better healthcare (Nairobi), larger expat community, more developed infrastructure. Many expats use both—live Tanzania, healthcare Kenya.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Tanzania coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Tanzania authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
